s</a> of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rational_function" title=
=3D"Rational function">rational functions</a>. Partial fraction decompositi=
on of real <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rational_function" titl=
e=3D"Rational function">rational functions</a> is also used to find their <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inverse_Laplace_transform" title=3D=
"Inverse Laplace transform">Inverse Laplace transforms</a>. For application=
s of <b>partial fraction decomposition over the reals</b>, see
</p>
<ul><li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Partial_fraction_decomposi=
tion#Application_to_symbolic_integration">Application to symbolic integrati=
on</a>, above</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Partial_fractions_in_Laplace_t=
ransforms" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Partial fractions in Laplace tran=
sforms">Partial fractions in Laplace transforms</a></li></ul>
