l-align: -2.338ex; width:38.348ex; height:5.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle f=
(x)=3D{\frac {1}{x^{2}+2x-3}}=3D{\frac {A}{x+3}}+{\frac {B}{x-1}}}"></span>
</p><p>Multiplying through by the denominator on the left-hand side gives u=
s the polynomial identity
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle 1=3DA(x-1)+B(x+3)}">
