        <mn>1</mn>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>B</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>3</mn>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 1=3DA(x-1)+B(=
x+3)}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/319abda15cd08fbd75e17d28da4ceaedc9cb1706" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.838ex; width:24.892ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle 1=
=3DA(x-1)+B(x+3)}"></span>
</p><p>Substituting <i>x</i>  =3D =E2=88=923 into this equation gives <i>A<=
/i> =3D =E2=88=921/4, and substituting <i>x</i>  =3D 1 gives <i>B</i> =3D 1=
/4, so that
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle f(x)=3D{\frac {1}{x^{2}+2x-3}}=3D{\frac {1}{4}}\left({\=
frac {-1}{x+3}}+{\frac {1}{x-1}}\right)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
