=3DD(x-(2-2i))+E(x-(2+2i))}"></span>
</p><p>Equating the coefficients of <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i></span>=
 and the constant (with respect to <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i></span>)=
 coefficients of both sides of this equation, one gets a system of two line=
ar equations in <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>D</i></span> and <span class=3D"=
texhtml"><i>E</i></span>, whose solution is
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle D=3D{\frac {1+i}{2i}}=3D{\frac {1-i}{2}},\qquad E=3D{\f=
rac {1-i}{-2i}}=3D{\frac {1+i}{2}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
