<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Example_5_(limit_method)"><=
span id=3D"Example_5_.28limit_method.29"></span>Example 5 (limit method)</h=
3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</=
span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DPartial_fracti=
on_decomposition&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D17" title=3D"Edit section:=
 Example 5 (limit method)"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsecti=
on-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Limit_(mathematics)" title=3D"L=
imit (mathematics)">Limits</a> can be used to find a partial fraction decom=
position.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Partial_fraction_decomposition#cite_note-4"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> =
Consider the following example:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle {\frac {1}{x^{3}-1}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mrow>
              <msup>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>3</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>1</mn>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\frac {1}{x^=
{3}-1}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/e9e7f7b8a855b25547ad9bec751995fe1c1febea" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.338ex; width:7.223ex; height:5.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
frac {1}{x^{3}-1}}}"></span>
</p><p>First, factor the denominator which determines the decomposition:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle {\frac {1}{x^{3}-1}}=3D{\frac {1}{(x-1)(x^{2}+x+1)}}=3D=
{\frac {A}{x-1}}+{\frac {Bx+C}{x^{2}+x+1}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mrow>
              <msup>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>3</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>1</mn>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>1</mn>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <msup>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>1</mn>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mi>A</mi>
            <mrow>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>1</mn>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
