      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \lim _{x\to \=
infty }{\frac {x}{(x-1)(x^{2}+x+1)}}=3D0.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/242b0fff39e05c4e74185fbab38a89a99adfffb8" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.671ex; width:29.865ex; height:5.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
lim _{x\to \infty }{\frac {x}{(x-1)(x^{2}+x+1)}}=3D0.}"></span>
</p><p>This implies <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>A</i> + <i>B</i> =3D 0</span=
> and so <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span cla=
ss=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"=
><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaysty=
le B=3D-{\frac {1}{3}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>B</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mn>3</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle B=3D-{\frac {=
1}{3}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/b3564a61f378d8cd1a8e9e3e122915cc8efa6133" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.838ex; width:8.669ex; height:5.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle B=
=3D-{\frac {1}{3}}}"></span>.
</p><p>For <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i> =3D 0</span>, we get  <span cla=
ss=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mat=
hml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"ht=
tp://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle -1=3D-A+C,}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>C</mi>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle -1=3D-A+C,}</=
annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/f8030e4c0668a0c33eb9ed6aa219ce7e1dbfc470" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:14.874ex; height:2.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle -1=
=3D-A+C,}"></span> and thus  <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-eleme=
nt-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" styl=
e=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alt=
text=3D"{\displaystyle C=3D-{\tfrac {2}{3}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>C</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
            <mfrac>
              <mn>2</mn>
              <mn>3</mn>
            </mfrac>
          </mstyle>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle C=3D-{\tfrac =
{2}{3}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/0f7517b3b92ba2e866a576264466a2b9617e3704" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.338ex; width:8.331ex; height:3.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle C=
=3D-{\tfrac {2}{3}}}"></span>.
</p><p>Putting everything together, we get the decomposition
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle {\frac {1}{x^{3}-1}}=3D{\frac {1}{3}}\left({\frac {1}{x=
-1}}+{\frac {-x-2}{x^{2}+x+1}}\right).}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mrow>
              <msup>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>3</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>1</mn>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mn>3</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mfrac>
                <mn>1</mn>
                <mrow>
                  <mi>x</mi>
                  <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                  <mn>1</mn>
                </mrow>
              </mfrac>
            </mrow>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mfrac>
                <mrow>
                  <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                  <mi>x</mi>
                  <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
                <mrow>
                  <msup>
                    <mi>x</mi>
                    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                      <mn>2</mn>
                    </mrow>
                  </msup>
                  <mo>+</mo>
                  <mi>x</mi>
                  <mo>+</mo>
                  <mn>1</mn>
                </mrow>
              </mfrac>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\frac {1}{x^=
{3}-1}}=3D{\frac {1}{3}}\left({\frac {1}{x-1}}+{\frac {-x-2}{x^{2}+x+1}}\ri=
ght).}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/ccfe2f1e7853fdba7ee57c662b28a21f659a351e" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.505ex; width:37.564ex; height:6.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {=
\frac {1}{x^{3}-1}}=3D{\frac {1}{3}}\left({\frac {1}{x-1}}+{\frac {-x-2}{x^=
{2}+x+1}}\right).}"></span>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Example_6_(integral)"><span=
 id=3D"Example_6_.28integral.29"></span>Example 6 (integral)</h3><span clas=
s=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DPartial_fraction_decomposi=
tion&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D18" title=3D"Edit section: Example 6 (=
integral)"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</s=
pan></span></div>
<p>Suppose we have the indefinite <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Integral" title=3D"Integral">integral</a>:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle \int {\frac {x^{4}+x^{3}+x^{2}+1}{x^{2}+x-2}}\,dx}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mo>=E2=88=AB<!-- =E2=88=AB --></mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <msup>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>4</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <msup>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>3</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <msup>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>1</mn>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <msup>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>2</mn>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mspace width=3D"thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mi>d</mi>
        <mi>x</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \int {\frac {=
x^{4}+x^{3}+x^{2}+1}{x^{2}+x-2}}\,dx}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/4ab6508e87c86a4b05af53e3944f5c5cd5667ce1" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.338ex; width:23.185ex; height:6.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
int {\frac {x^{4}+x^{3}+x^{2}+1}{x^{2}+x-2}}\,dx}"></span>
</p><p>Before performing decomposition, it is obvious we must perform polyn=
omial long division and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Factorizat=
ion" title=3D"Factorization">factor</a> the denominator. Doing this would r=
esult in:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle \int \left(x^{2}+3+{\frac {-3x+7}{(x+2)(x-1)}}\right)dx=
}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mo>=E2=88=AB<!-- =E2=88=AB --></mo>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
            <msup>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>2</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msup>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mn>3</mn>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mfrac>
                <mrow>
                  <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                  <mn>3</mn>
                  <mi>x</mi>
                  <mo>+</mo>
                  <mn>7</mn>
                </mrow>
                <mrow>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
                  <mi>x</mi>
                  <mo>+</mo>
                  <mn>2</mn>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
                  <mi>x</mi>
                  <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                  <mn>1</mn>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
                </mrow>
              </mfrac>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mi>d</mi>
        <mi>x</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \int \left(x^=
{2}+3+{\frac {-3x+7}{(x+2)(x-1)}}\right)dx}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/3a711e9052fe7f80b77989a99d512b2c1b44dcbe" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.671ex; width:33.282ex; height:6.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
int \left(x^{2}+3+{\frac {-3x+7}{(x+2)(x-1)}}\right)dx}"></span>
</p><p>Upon this, we may now perform partial fraction decomposition.
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle \int \left(x^{2}+3+{\frac {-3x+7}{(x+2)(x-1)}}\right)dx=
=3D\int \left(x^{2}+3+{\frac {A}{(x+2)}}+{\frac {B}{(x-1)}}\right)dx}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mo>=E2=88=AB<!-- =E2=88=AB --></mo>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
            <msup>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>2</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msup>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mn>3</mn>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mfrac>
                <mrow>
                  <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                  <mn>3</mn>
                  <mi>x</mi>
                  <mo>+</mo>
                  <mn>7</mn>
                </mrow>
                <mrow>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
                  <mi>x</mi>
                  <mo>+</mo>
                  <mn>2</mn>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
                  <mi>x</mi>
                  <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                  <mn>1</mn>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
                </mrow>
              </mfrac>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mi>d</mi>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo>=E2=88=AB<!-- =E2=88=AB --></mo>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
            <msup>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>2</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msup>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mn>3</mn>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mfrac>
                <mi>A</mi>
                <mrow>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
                  <mi>x</mi>
                  <mo>+</mo>
                  <mn>2</mn>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
                </mrow>
              </mfrac>
            </mrow>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mfrac>
                <mi>B</mi>
                <mrow>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
                  <mi>x</mi>
                  <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                  <mn>1</mn>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
                </mrow>
              </mfrac>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mi>d</mi>
        <mi>x</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \int \left(x^=
{2}+3+{\frac {-3x+7}{(x+2)(x-1)}}\right)dx=3D\int \left(x^{2}+3+{\frac {A}{=
(x+2)}}+{\frac {B}{(x-1)}}\right)dx}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/7d67255f262c61c37a4f438b3e227799fe734d20" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.671ex; width:73.338ex; height:6.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
int \left(x^{2}+3+{\frac {-3x+7}{(x+2)(x-1)}}\right)dx=3D\int \left(x^{2}+3=
+{\frac {A}{(x+2)}}+{\frac {B}{(x-1)}}\right)dx}"></span>
so:
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle A(x-1)+B(x+2)=3D-3x+7}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>B</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>2</mn>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mn>3</mn>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>7</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle A(x-1)+B(x+2)=
=3D-3x+7}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/895d0fda6783c4c54d9f301c54823d94498a0fff" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.838ex; width:32.033ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle A=
(x-1)+B(x+2)=3D-3x+7}"></span>.
Upon substituting our values, in this case, where x=3D1 to solve for B and =
x=3D-2 to solve for A, we will result in:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle A=3D{\frac {-13}{3}}\ ,B=3D{\frac {4}{3}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>13</mn>
            </mrow>
            <mn>3</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mtext>&nbsp;</mtext>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mi>B</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>4</mn>
            <mn>3</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle A=3D{\frac {-=
13}{3}}\ ,B=3D{\frac {4}{3}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/56b64201f348df7aa3c67d242136fa1678e02c44" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -1.838ex; width:18.286ex; height:5.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle A=
=3D{\frac {-13}{3}}\ ,B=3D{\frac {4}{3}}}"></span>
</p><p>Plugging all of this back into our integral allows us to find the an=
swer:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
