span></div>
<p>The partial fraction decomposition of a rational function can be related=
 to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taylor%27s_theorem" title=3D"T=
aylor's theorem">Taylor's theorem</a> as follows. Let
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle P(x),Q(x),A_{1}(x),\ldots ,A_{r}(x)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>P</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mi>Q</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>A</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mo>=E2=80=A6<!-- =E2=80=A6 --></mo>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>A</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>r</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle P(x),Q(x),A_{=
1}(x),\ldots ,A_{r}(x)}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/e7603a5844c6bb442799fbdcd6e9d586ab7711ce" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.838ex; width:28.9ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle P(x=
),Q(x),A_{1}(x),\ldots ,A_{r}(x)}"></span>
</p><p>be real or complex polynomials=20
assume that
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle Q=3D\prod _{j=3D1}^{r}(x-\lambda _{j})^{\nu _{j}},}">
